VARIOUS support groups under the auspices of New Tribe Nigeria has endorsed Vice President Yemi Osinbajo as the most credible person to succeed the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), in 2023. In a communiqué issued in Kano on Sunday, at the end of a one-day declaration conference, the support group noted that after a critical analysis of achievements and performances of the Buhari regime despite the severe economic and security challenges, Osinbajo’s pedigree remains the best choice for the nation. The group stated, “The conference resolved that the choice of Osinbajo is to press for continued corporate existence, progress and unity of the New Tribe-Nigeria. ‘’We want to push for continuity and sustainability of ongoing landmark developmental projects, embarked upon by President Muhammadu Buhari’s administration. ‘’We resolved to mobilise Nigerians of all faith and tribe to support the enthronement of a just man, who understand policies and programmes of  President Buhari’s administration.” It urged the All Progressives Congress to nominate Osinbajo as its Presidential candidate for the 2023 presidential election for consolidation and continuity of the APC overall stability. The conference called on the Vice President to heed the call of Nigerians and declare his intention to run for President. Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com